<subSubSection id="C355E1A6FFFB2561FF41FABBFD083266" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFB2561FF41FABBFED5314D" blockId="1.[189,310,1321,1347]" box="[189,310,1321,1347]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<heading id="D0B80541FFFB2561FF41FABBFED5314D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1321,1347]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FF41FABBFED5314D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1321,1347]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFB2561FF41FAC5FD083266" blockId="1.[189,1399,1367,1640]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Monospecific genus externally very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FD1DFACAFCAA317C" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[737,841,1368,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FD1DFACAFCAA317C" box="[737,841,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FC7FFAC5FC01317F" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[899,994,1367,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FC7FFAC5FC01317F" box="[899,994,1367,1393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Differential characters: two basal bands on the forewings upperside (a single basal band in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FC8AFAE9FC36319B" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[886,981,1403,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FC8AFAE9FC36319B" box="[886,981,1403,1429]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); bipectinate antennae of the male (filiform or serrate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FE3CFA0CFDCB31B6" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[448,552,1438,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FE3CFA0CFDCB31B6" box="[448,552,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FD98FA0CFD2031B6" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[612,707,1438,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FD98FA0CFD2031B6" box="[612,707,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); spur formula 0-4-4 (0-2- 
<quantity id="4CB71FC8FFFB2561FC03FA0CFBCD31B6" box="[1023,1070,1438,1464]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FBCAFA0CFB7631B6" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[1078,1173,1438,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FBCAFA0CFB7631B6" box="[1078,1173,1438,1464]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); coremata absent; uncus long and slender, clubbed (shorter, often curved, ending in a point in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FBA2FA53FB2531D5" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[1118,1222,1473,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FBA2FA53FB2531D5" box="[1118,1222,1473,1499]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FAFAFA53FA8631D5" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[1286,1381,1473,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FAFAFA53FA8631D5" box="[1286,1381,1473,1499]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); tegumen strong; scaphium well sclerotized; distal end of the valva undivided, with a finger-like process (valve clearly divided valva in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FDDBF99AFD6C322C" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[551,655,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FDDBF99AFD6C322C" box="[551,655,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; a different kind of distal process present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FB64F995FB14322F" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[1176,1271,1543,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FB64F995FB14322F" box="[1176,1271,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); presence of the processus distalis plicae (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FD57F9B9FCF0324B" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[683,787,1579,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FD57F9B9FCF0324B" box="[683,787,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); vinculum without saccus; vesica with a cluster of very small and sparse thorns; no strong cornuti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C355E1A6FFFB2561FF41F91DFC6F32F5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFB2561FF41F91DFEA732A7" blockId="1.[189,324,1679,1705]" box="[189,324,1679,1705]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<heading id="D0B80541FFFB2561FF41F91DFEA732A7" bold="true" box="[189,324,1679,1705]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FF41F91DFEA732A7" bold="true" box="[189,324,1679,1705]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFB2561FF41F92CFC6F32F5" blockId="1.[189,1398,1726,1788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The prefix “para”, from ancient Greek, means “similar to” and indicates the probable relationship with the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FEC8F973FE7F32F5" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[308,412,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FEC8F973FE7F32F5" box="[308,412,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender of the new name is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C355E1A6FFFB2563FF41F8B0FD9237DF" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFB2561FF41F8B0FEAD3332" blockId="1.[189,334,1826,1852]" box="[189,334,1826,1852]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<heading id="D0B80541FFFB2561FF41F8B0FEAD3332" bold="true" box="[189,334,1826,1852]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FF41F8B0FEAD3332" bold="true" box="[189,334,1826,1852]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFB2561FF41F8C3FBAF3380" blockId="1.[189,1399,1873,1935]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The descriptions of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFFB2561FE54F8C3FD4C3365" author="Bethune-Baker G. T." box="[424,687,1873,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="530 - 552" refId="ref5232" refString="Bethune-Baker G. T. 1911. Descriptions of new African Heterocera. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, vol. 7, VIII series: 530 - 552." type="journal article" year="1911">Bethune-Baker (1911)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFFB2561FD14F8C0FC4D3365" author="Hampson G. F." box="[744,942,1873,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" refId="ref5628" refString="Hampson G. F. 1914. Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. Supplement. Volume I. British Museum (Natural History), London." type="book" year="1914">Hampson (1914)</bibRefCitation>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFB2561FC2BF8C3FB723365" authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1911" box="[983,1169,1873,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFB2561FC2BF8C3FB723365" box="[983,1169,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Asura pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are comprehensive enough with regard to external appearance of its body and wings (
<figureCitation id="1374AEA8FFFB2561FC38F8E6FBE63380" box="[964,1029,1908,1934]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[267,1322,275,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[252,1337,265,1846]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Parafrasura pectinella (Strand, 1922). A. Holotype Ƌ, Angola, in BMNH. B. Ƌ, Democratic Republic of the Congo, in BMNH. C. Ƌ, Cameroun, in BMNH. D. Enlarged Fig. B, showing the basal bands of the forewing. E. Ƌ, head of Fig. C enlarged, showing the bipectinate antennae. F. Ƌ genitalia, g.sl. BM ARCT 5741, Chad. G. Aedeagus, g.sl. BM ARCT 5741, Chad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3858305/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A-E).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF30E2A5FFF82562FF41F8F6FBEA33E6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858305" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3858305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3858305/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" startId="2.[189,232,1892,1918]" targetBox="[267,1322,275,1838]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF82562FF41F8F6FBEA33E6" blockId="2.[189,1399,1892,2025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FF41F8F6FEEE3370" bold="true" box="[189,269,1892,1918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF82562FEEBF8F7FD3F3371" authority="(Strand, 1922)" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Strand" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[279,732,1892,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Parafrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinella">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FEEBF8F7FDC53371" box="[279,550,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Parafrasura pectinella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFF82562FDC4F8F6FD373371" author="Strand E." box="[568,724,1892,1919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="501 - 899" refId="ref6231" refString="Strand E. 1922. Arctiidae: Subfam. Lithosiinae. In: Wagner H. (ed.), Lepidopterorum Catalogus, 15 - 16 (26): 501 - 899. Junk, Berlin &amp; The Hague." type="journal article" year="1922">Strand, 1922</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FD10F8F6FCE23370" bold="true" box="[748,769,1892,1918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">A</emphasis>
. Holotype Ƌ, Angola, in BMNH. 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FB5DF8F7FB563371" bold="true" box="[1185,1205,1893,1919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">B</emphasis>
. Ƌ, Democratic Republic of the Congo, in BMNH. 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FD9EF81AFD9433AC" bold="true" box="[610,631,1928,1954]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">C</emphasis>
. Ƌ, Cameroun, in BMNH. 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FC44F81AFC2E33AC" bold="true" box="[952,973,1928,1954]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">D</emphasis>
. Enlarged Fig. B, showing the basal bands of the forewing. 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FE31F839FE0233CB" bold="true" box="[461,481,1963,1989]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. Ƌ, head of Fig. C enlarged, showing the bipectinate antennae. 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FB30F839FB3D33CB" bold="true" box="[1228,1246,1963,1989]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">F</emphasis>
. Ƌ genitalia, g.sl. BM ARCT 5741, Chad. 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF82562FDE8F85CFDC833E6" bold="true" box="[532,555,1998,2024]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">G</emphasis>
. Aedeagus, g.sl. BM ARCT 5741, Chad.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FE9EFDB73562" blockId="3.[189,1399,267,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">MALE ABDOMEN. With VII and VIII urites smaller than the previous ones. VIII sternum with anterior margin slightly waved; VIII tergum anterior margin with a bar-like reinforcement with two small apodemes at its lateral extremities.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FE01FAC73653" blockId="3.[189,1399,403,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
GENITALIA. (
<figureCitation id="1374AEA8FFF92563FEB4FE01FE6A35A3" box="[328,393,403,429]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[267,1322,275,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[252,1337,265,1846]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Parafrasura pectinella (Strand, 1922). A. Holotype Ƌ, Angola, in BMNH. B. Ƌ, Democratic Republic of the Congo, in BMNH. C. Ƌ, Cameroun, in BMNH. D. Enlarged Fig. B, showing the basal bands of the forewing. E. Ƌ, head of Fig. C enlarged, showing the bipectinate antennae. F. Ƌ genitalia, g.sl. BM ARCT 5741, Chad. G. Aedeagus, g.sl. BM ARCT 5741, Chad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3858305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
F-G) With uncus long and slender, claviform. Tegumen large and short, stronger than usually found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FE80FE25FE2135DF" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[380,450,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FE80FE25FE2135DF" box="[380,450,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Asura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like genera (i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FD7FFE25FD2A35DF" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[643,713,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FD7FFE25FD2A35DF" box="[643,713,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Asura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FD2AFE25FCDD35DF" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[726,830,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FD2AFE25FCDD35DF" box="[726,830,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FCB7FE24FC4935DE" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[843,938,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FCB7FE24FC4935DE" box="[843,938,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Posteriorly to the tegumen, two strong arms arise and suddenly meet together, forming a strong sclerotized structure (gnathos), which includes the sclerotized dorsal surface of the tuba analis (scaphium). Vinculum. Slender, semicircular, without saccus, tightly linked to the valvae. Anellus dorsally with a slightly sclerotized W-shaped transtilla, and ventrally with a quite large dome-shaped membranous juxta, not visible in the slide preparation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FD17FAA93707" blockId="3.[189,1399,645,777]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
VALVA. Slightly widening from the base to the distal margin, linked to the vinculum except for the costa. Two longitudinal swellings extending parallel from base to the distal 4/5: the first one just under the costal margin, the second one along the inferior margin (ala valvae of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFF92563FC09FD59FB3636E8" author="Birket-Smith J." box="[1013,1237,715,742]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref5264" refString="Birket-Smith J. 1965. A revision of the West African Eilemic Moths, based on the Male Genitalia. (Lep., Arctiidae, Lithosinae; incl. gen. Crocosia, Eilema, Lithosia, Pelosia, Phryganopsis a. o.). Papers from the Faculty of Science. Series C (Zoology) No. 1, Haile Sellassie I University, Addis Ababa." type="book" year="1965">Birket-Smith 1965</bibRefCitation>
). At the apex, the valva possesses a keel-like enlargement; at the middle of the distal margin a finger-like process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FCA2FB9B3744" blockId="3.[189,1144,816,842]" box="[189,1144,816,842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">AEDEAGUS. Small, tubular, with a bulbous coecum. Vesica with sparse tiny thorns.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FCE0FD9237DF" blockId="3.[189,1399,881,977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
FEMALE GENITALIA. These have not been directly examined, but the described characteristics (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFF92563FAE3FCE3FED037A1" author="Kuhne L." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="353 - 394" refId="ref6030" refString="Kuhne L. 2007. Beschreibung neuer Flechtenbarenarten aus Afrika nebst taxonomischen Anmerkungen (Arctiidae: Lithosiinae). Esperiana Memoir, 3: 353 - 394, pls. 44, 45." type="book chapter" year="2007">Kühne, 2007: 365</bibRefCitation>
) seem to be exclusive, particularly the sclerotizations of the ostium bursae and the bag-shaped invagination proximad of the ostium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C355E1A6FFF92564FF41FC6BFE373672" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FC6BFECC301D" blockId="3.[189,303,1017,1043]" box="[189,303,1017,1043]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="D0B80541FFF92563FF41FC6BFECC301D" bold="true" box="[189,303,1017,1043]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FF41FC6BFECC301D" bold="true" box="[189,303,1017,1043]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FBBAFD2930A2" blockId="3.[189,1398,1063,1196]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FF41FBBAFDC5304C" authority="Strand, 1922" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,550,1063,1090]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinella">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FF41FBBAFE61304F" box="[189,386,1063,1090]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Asura pectinella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFF92563FE70FBB5FDC5304C" author="Strand E." box="[396,550,1063,1090]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="501 - 899" refId="ref6231" refString="Strand E. 1922. Arctiidae: Subfam. Lithosiinae. In: Wagner H. (ed.), Lepidopterorum Catalogus, 15 - 16 (26): 501 - 899. Junk, Berlin &amp; The Hague." type="journal article" year="1922">Strand, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was firstly described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFF92563FCA6FBB5FB87304C" author="Bethune-Baker G. T." box="[858,1124,1063,1090]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="530 - 552" refId="ref5232" refString="Bethune-Baker G. T. 1911. Descriptions of new African Heterocera. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, vol. 7, VIII series: 530 - 552." type="journal article" year="1911">Bethune-Baker (1911)</bibRefCitation>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FAF1FBBAFAB0304C" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[1293,1363,1064,1090]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FAF1FBBAFAB0304C" box="[1293,1363,1064,1090]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Asura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FF41FBD9FEA8306B" authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1911" box="[189,331,1099,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FF41FBD9FEA8306B" box="[189,331,1099,1125]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">A. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FEA0FBDEFE18306B" box="[348,507,1100,1125]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">nom. praeocc</emphasis>
.); the genitalia morphology, however, leads to the conclusion, that it should be included in a genus of its own. Already 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDECFDCFFF92563FD3BFBFCFC8E3086" author="Kuhne L." box="[711,877,1134,1160]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="353 - 394" refId="ref6030" refString="Kuhne L. 2007. Beschreibung neuer Flechtenbarenarten aus Afrika nebst taxonomischen Anmerkungen (Arctiidae: Lithosiinae). Esperiana Memoir, 3: 353 - 394, pls. 44, 45." type="book chapter" year="2007">Kühne (2007)</bibRefCitation>
rightly separated this species in a group of itself, however leaving it in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FD81FB00FD2030A2" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[637,707,1170,1196]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FD81FB00FD2030A2" box="[637,707,1170,1196]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Asura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41FB41FA94311E" blockId="3.[189,1399,1234,1296]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
A new genus is here described after the examination of specimens from Western and Central Africa, whose size and wing pattern are very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FD10FB64FCB7311E" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[748,852,1270,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FD10FB64FCB7311E" box="[748,852,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1374AEA8FFF92563FC98FB64FC23311E" box="[868,960,1270,1296]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[194,1392,1338,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[187,1399,1334,1915]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. — A. Afrasura indecisa, holotype Ƌ, Congo, in BMNH. — B. Tumicla sagenaria, holotype Ƌ, South Africa, in NHRS." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3858307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FBFDFB64FB83311E" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1860" box="[1025,1120,1270,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FBFDFB64FB83311E" box="[1025,1120,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Tumicla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1374AEA8FFF92563FB93FB64FB28311E" box="[1135,1227,1270,1296]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[194,1392,1338,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[187,1399,1334,1915]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. — A. Afrasura indecisa, holotype Ƌ, Congo, in BMNH. — B. Tumicla sagenaria, holotype Ƌ, South Africa, in NHRS." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3858307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). However the
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF30E2A5FFF92563FF41F834FE3633ED" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3858307" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3858307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3858307/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" startId="3.[189,232,1958,1984]" targetBox="[194,1392,1338,1910]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFF92563FF41F834FE3633ED" blockId="3.[189,1398,1958,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FF41F834FEAF33CE" bold="true" box="[189,332,1958,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2. — A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FEA0F834FDCD33CE" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[348,558,1958,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indecisa">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FEA0F834FDCD33CE" box="[348,558,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Afrasura indecisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype Ƌ, Congo, in BMNH. — 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FC20F834FC1333CE" bold="true" box="[988,1008,1958,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFF92563FC03F834FB3933CE" baseAuthorityName="Wallengren" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1023,1242,1958,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Tumicla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagenaria">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFF92563FC03F834FB3933CE" box="[1023,1242,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Tumicla sagenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype Ƌ, South Africa, in NHRS.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFE2564FF41FE99FBD63544" blockId="4.[189,1398,267,330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">male bipectinate antennae and genitalic peculiarities are here considered strongly distinctive and have never before been observed in the aforementioned, probably related genera.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFE2564FF41FEE0FA8935BE" blockId="4.[189,1398,370,432]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The new genus shows a wing venation and pattern very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFE2564FBE6FEE0FB613582" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[1050,1154,370,396]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFE2564FBE6FEE0FB613582" box="[1050,1154,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so that the venation and the two basal bands are considered synapomorphic characters of the 
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFE2564FBEFFE04FAF535BE" box="[1043,1302,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFE2564FBEFFE04FB9835BE" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[1043,1147,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Afrasura</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFE2564FB79FE04FAF535BE" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2012" box="[1157,1302,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Parafrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Parafrasura</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFE2564FF41FE4AFCFE3618" blockId="4.[189,1398,472,534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Probable autapomorphies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FC9AEFFFE2564FDEAFE4AFD4435FC" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2012" box="[534,679,472,498]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Parafrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93B6E3FFFFE2564FDEAFE4AFD4435FC" box="[534,679,472,498]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Parafrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: tegumen strong and large; uncus long, slender, slightly claviform; shape of the scaphium-gnathos complex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0B22DFFFE2564FF41FDACFE373672" blockId="4.[189,1398,574,636]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Other relevant characters are: male antennae bipectinate; female with short anterior apophyses and sinus vaginalis conformation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
